The expression of a gene is the appearance of an observable feature or action caused by the effect of the protein encoded by this gene. Gene regulation is the mechanism which determines the amount of protein product that must be syntesized by switching the genes responsible for that protein on or off. Only a subset of genes in an eukaryotic cell are expressed at each instant, considerably changing this regulational composition during the life cycle.
\end_layout

