Transcription regulation and animal diversity are intimately associated. For example, despite the number of genes in common between two different species as human and mouse is extremely high, both animals present different organismal complexity. Emerging evidence suggests that a more sophisticate elaboration of the regulatory mechanisms can be the responsible of this great variability 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
after ""
before ""
key "levine:2003a"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

